# Playtest notes / backlog

## Done
- [x] to few enemies — complexity packs (1 extra enemy per 10 pts) [Task 18]
- [x] increase aggro distance — 5 → 7.5 tiles [Task 18]
- [x] enemies sometimes invisible when very close to the player — sprite near-clip fix [Task 18]
- [x] enemies shouldnt be melee only — ranged plasma bolts [Task 19]
- [x] enemies should roam around in their rooms, not wait statically (without leaving the room) [Task 18]
- [x] enemies dont attack when shot from outside aggro distance — damage aggro [Task 18]
- [x] return and enemy placed at the same location — exit tile kept clear of spawns [Task 18]
- [x] to less ammo — defeated enemies drop heap (ammo) pickups [Task 11]
- [x] strafing — A/D strafe perpendicular to the camera [Task 20]
- [x] running — Shift sprints at 2x move speed [Task 20]
- [x] floors to long / paths boring — long corridors now jog/turn instead of one straight sightline; large rooms get 1-3 pillars to break up empty space [Task 21]
- [x] goto usage should result in a teleport portal, like they exist in e.g UT — `goto`/label pairs are now parsed (C + PHP) and turned into linked, glowing violet teleporter pad pairs; stepping on one warps to the other [Task 22]
- [x] multi-level / jump to next level on end of level — reaching `return` now auto-loads the next parsable file in the tree (depth-first, dirs-first) instead of ending the run, carrying health/ammo across; only shows the win screen on the last file [Task 22]
- [x] add languages: asm, js, ts, python, java, c++, objc (and other realworld languages, as long as supported by our libs - we dont want to use multiple libs for that) — added JS, TS/TSX, Python, Java, C++, Go, Rust, Ruby, C#, Bash, Scala, Objective-C via one generic Tree-sitter-driven adapter (still just tree-sitter, no second parsing lib); no ASM (no ABI-compatible prebuilt grammar found), Kotlin/Lua skipped (no prebuilt wasm shipped by their packages) [Task 23]
- [x] ensure code parser only acts on actual supported code, in case some troll loads his meme folder or whatever. ensure that loaded code is never executed. — strict extension whitelist (only registered adapters' extensions reach a parser at all), plus a size cap + binary-content sniff on top; loaded text is only ever fed to `Parser.parse()` (builds an AST), never eval'd/compiled/run; any parse failure now logs a warning and skips the file instead of crashing the map generator or game loop [Task 23]
- [x] map top left should be semi-transparent. player and direction should be more clearly visible, same for the exit. enemies shouldnt be show until the room was entered. — always-on minimap now uses a semi-transparent dark rgba backing panel, a bright solid triangle for the player's exact position/facing, a pulsing high-contrast exit marker, and enemies stay hidden until the player's collision box AABB-intersects their room (sticky once discovered) [Task 24]
- [x] more traps (kinds, but also placement) — added timed spike traps (tile toggles safe/damaging on a per-trap cycle) and invisible proximity mines (reveal + detonate for AoE damage if you linger, timer resets if you back off in time), both scattered procedurally at 1-tile-wide corridor choke points rather than open room floor. Not exhaustive — more kinds/placement variety is still open for later [Task 24]
- [x] if the AST has a detectable entrypoint (like `main()` for c, index.php for PHP etc), use that a starting level after loading the workspace — workspace load now searches for a standard entrypoint filename (main.c/cpp/py/go/rs, index.php, index.js, Program.cs, etc.) across the whole tree, falling back to a content-based `main()` function scan for the C family, and auto-launches it immediately; falls back further to the first parsable file in tree order if nothing matches [Task 24]
- [x] mines need to be visible way earlier, its almost impossible to avoid them — sight radius (visible) and fuse-arming radius (actually dangerous) are now separate: mines reveal from 4.5 tiles away but only start their fuse within 1.8, giving real reaction room. Also added the ability to shoot a spotted mine to disarm it outright — safe from beyond its blast radius, but still hurts point-blank — since spotting one you can't do anything about wasn't useful

## Open
- [ ] rooms need deco of some kind, currently an empty wasteland — implemented in Task 21 (server racks/plants/desks/code-blocks as billboard props) but felt annoying in playtest, so disabled again behind `DECORATIONS_ENABLED = false` in mapGenerator.ts. Code (generation + rendering) is intact; needs a design rethink (placement density? different visual treatment? non-billboard approach?) before re-enabling. Ignore for now.
- [ ] scoring (HUD has a Score slot since Task 20, always 0 — no scoring logic yet), extra points for health, ammo left, path length (shorter = better) and time needed (faster = better) at end of level, plus points for every kill (depending on enemy). score malus at end of level for health below 100%
- [ ] persisted highscore list
- [ ] makefile
- [ ] tests (unit [coverage target 100%!], end2end/functional/visual [coverage target: all aspects of gameplay])
- [ ] github ci actions for the tests (to be executed on github, no custom runner)
- [ ] ability to load github repos instead of local folder
- [ ] user pickable bgm folder — needs a simple settings menu for volume control (Master, SFX, BGM) so custom music doesn't overpower game audio
- [ ] scoresystem should also store a hash (sha256 or similar) of the AST, or code scanned. this should also be displayed in the highscore list, for comparison
- [ ] more weapons, to be randomly dropped by enemies. Like a rocket-like-launcher for AoE damage, or an MP.
- [ ] each weapon should use unique ammo, also resulting in a slightly but noticeable different tracer
- [ ] ammo should also be randomly placed across maps for player pickup, only as a sparse backup - primary source should be spawn + loot.
- [ ] fps (if possible: also gpu/cpu usage) display, toggable - default off. use RIGHT_CTRL as hotkey (for now)
- [ ] optional replay storage at end of level (even possible?)
- [ ] pause game if canvas not focussed / ESC was pressed
- [ ] gamepad/joystick support
- [ ] weapon should be rendered differently, depending on their type/strength
- [ ] fullscreen support for the canvas
- [ ] user/player docs in `doc/user`
- [ ] dev docs, GDD, design descisions etc in `doc/dev`
- [ ] ensure the player spawns far enough outside the aggro range of any enemy, except that's not possible without leaving the room
- [ ] collectible health and armor drops (randomly dropped on top of ammo by enemies)
- [ ] canvas looses focus on level change - bug
- [ ] weapons should have a range determined by their type (or realistic equivalent) — hitscan weapons should use a "Cone of Fire" (spread angle that widens with distance) instead of a hard drop-off to 0 damage
- [ ] drop, enemies, exit etc should be in front based on drawing distance from POV - for example: sometimes a dropped item next to exit "disappears" behind the exit
- [ ] player needs an unlimited meelee weapon ("SIGKILL Knife" / "Refactoring Crowbar") to be able to continue when out of ammo until dead or looting ammo. should feature a small lifesteal effect (+1 HP) or force a guaranteed ammo drop on kill to encourage aggressive play
- [ ] level start screen - showing stats about AST and the resulting lvl (enemy, room etc count). if there is a detectable project name of the loaded workspace: use that as "campaign" name, if not: use directory name except its `src`, in that case use the upper level directory name. use the filename as level name. game should be paused till the player ack's that screen. Also add a "Commit Summary" (Level End Screen) showing stats like "X Lines refactored, Y Bugs squashed".
- [ ] secret rooms (Secrets) — parse AST for "Dead Code" (unreachable code, blocks after returns) or large comment blocks. generate these as hidden rooms off the main map, accessible via fake walls, containing high-value loot (mega-health, rocket ammo).
- [ ] elite enemies / bosses — instead of just spawning *more* enemies (complexity packs), functions with extreme cyclomatic complexity (e.g., massive legacy controllers) spawn a single Elite Enemy (different tint/sprite, 4x HP, high damage, guaranteed weapon drop).
- [ ] lore terminals — parse code comments (`//` or `/* */`) into interactable glowing wall textures. pressing 'E' opens a text popup with the original code comment.
- [ ] save & quit (campaign persistence) — save the current campaign state (current file, HP, ammo, score, weapons) to `localStorage`. add a "Continue Run" button in the main menu for navigating massive repositories over multiple sessions.